<div class="SectionInstructions breakDiv aviodPrint">
    <div class="instruction m-10">
        <p class="m-5">Instructions</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Use the buttons on the right hand side to switch between different sections of the report.
            </li>
            <li> Complete each section fully </li>
            <li>When all sections are completed use the "Submit" button to email the form directly to the ISM department.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="instruction m-10">
        <p class="m-5">Notes</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If the form is too large to email you will be requested to transfer to form the FTP server and you will be given and option to send an email informing the ISM department that you have done so. Alternatively you can reduce the number of attachments and try again.</li>
            <li> If the form is not saved when attempting to submit you will be prompted to save it. If you do not save the form it will not be submitted. </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="Section breakDiv">
    <div class="SectionHead">
        <u>Section 1</u> - General Details
    </div>
    <div class="SectionContent">
        <table class="table tblSection">
            <tr>
                <td width="10%"><p class="m-5">Ship:</p></td>
                <td width="40%">
                    <div class="form-group has-feedback">

                        <select class="form-control  col-md-12 GIRData" name="Ship" id="Child">
                            @*<option value="null">--Select Ship--</option>*@ @*RDBJ 10/08/2021 Commented*@
                            @if (ViewBag.ShipDatas != null)
                            {
                                foreach (var item in ViewBag.ShipDatas)
                                {
                                    if (ViewBag.ShipName == @item.Name)
                                    {
                                        <option value="@item.Code" selected>@item.Name</option>
                                    }
                                    else
                                    {
                                        <option value="@item.Code">@item.Name</option>
                                    }

                                }
                            }
                        </select>
                        <input type="hidden" name="ShipName" id="ShipName" />
                        @*<input type="hidden" id="Child" name="Ship" />
                        <input type="text" class="col-md-12 form-control GIRData" value="@OfficeApplication.BLL.Helpers.SessionManager.ShipName" readonly />*@

                        <span class="form-control-feedback">
                            @*<label class="text-danger">*</label>*@ @*RDBJ 10/08/2021 Commented*@
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </td>
                <td width="10%"><p class="m-5">Port:</p></td>
                <td width="40%">
                    <div class="form-group has-feedback">
                        <input type="text" class="col-md-12 form-control GIRData" id="Port" name="Port" />
                        <span class="form-control-feedback">
                            <label class="text-danger">*</label>
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td width="10%"><p class="m-5">Inspector:</p></td>
                <td width="40%">
                    <div class="form-group has-feedback">
                        @*<select class="col-md-12 form-control GIRData" id="Inspector" name="Inspector">
                            <option value=""></option>
                            <option>Angus Tapp</option>
                            <option>Bogdan Cojocaru</option>
                            <option>Bogdan Sokolowski</option>
                            <option>Krzysztof Nowaczyk</option>
